HEADWORD: Cancellous
<hw>Can"cel*lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. L.
<ets>cancellosus</ets> covered with bars.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Having a spongy or porous structure; made up of cancelli;
cancellated; <as>as, the <ex>cancellous</ex> texture of parts of many
bones</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

